: 3}, {"id": "https://www.technologyreview.com/?p=1135720", "title": "Why opinion on AI is so divided", "summary": "This story originally appeared in The Algorithm, our weekly newsletter on AI. To get stories like this in your inbox first, sign up here. In an industry that doesn\u2019t stand still, Stanford\u2019s AI Index, an annual roundup of key results and trends, is a chance to take a breath. (It\u2019s a marathon, not a s...", "link": "https://www.technologyreview.com/2026/04/13/1135720/why-opinion-on-ai-is-so-divided/", "source": "MIT Tech Review", "image": null, "score": 2}, {"id": "https://www.technologyreview.com/?p=1135675", "title": "Want to understand the current state of AI? Check out these charts.", "summary": "If you\u2019re following AI news, you\u2019re probably getting whiplash. AI is a gold rush. AI is a bubble. AI is taking your job. AI can\u2019t even read a clock. The 2026 AI Index from Stanford University\u2019s Institute for Human-Centered Artificial Intelligence, AI\u2019s annual report card, comes out today and cuts th...", "link": "https://www.technologyreview.com/2026/04/13/1135675/want-to-understand-the-current-state-of-ai-check-out-these-charts/", "source": "MIT Tech Review", "image": null, "score": 2}, {"id": "https://www.technologyreview.com/?p=1135156", "title": "Job titles of the future: Wildlife first responder", "summary": "Grizzly bears have made such a comeback across eastern Montana that in 2017, the state hired its first-ever prairie-based grizzly manager: wildlife biologist Wesley Sarmento.&#160; For some seven years, Sarmento worked to keep both the bears, which are still listed as threatened under the Endangered...", "link": "https://www.technologyreview.com/2026/04/13/1135156/job-titles-wildlife-first-responder-wesley-sarmento/", "source": "MIT Tech Review", "image": null, "score": 2}, {"id": "https://www.technologyreview.com/?p=1135162", "title": "You have no choice in reading this article\u2014maybe", "summary": "Uri Ma